I’m thankful for the opportunity to have run this race for the 3rd Congressional District, although I will not be advancing to the General Election. I want to thank all those who supported me in this effort - those who volunteered, donated, and prayed.

Instead they are only adding one auxiliary lane each direction. By their own words, commute times across the river will only be reduced by 3-11 minutes, and knowing their calculations, that’s probably generous. It’s time for a 3rd bridge now!

And the U.S. Coast Guard has said the bridge height has to be 60 ft. higher than planned. I will keep working for a 3rd bridge for you, our trucking industry, and business community!

They are not adding any more throughput lanes which would start reducing traffic congestion.

This I-5 bridge replacement project is the wrong project and will not help the people! It won’t significantly reduce commute times, it will have double tolls, and will bring light rail (a.k.a. more crime) to Vancouver. https://t.co/NAwC9uBWjq
SCOTUS has also reestablished the proper meaning behind church and state. This protects the people’s First Amendment rights. No longer twisting the words of Thomas Jefferson’s 1802 letters.
This highlights the importance of checks and balances. There are some other cases SCOTUS may need to re-evaluate in the future.

The Roe v. Wade decision is a win for the people. SCOTUS overstepped their boundaries when they originally created the laws regarding this issue. We are seeing a SCOTUS checking it’s own power. The Court has been making strides for the people this week.
We are the United States of America, one nation under GOD, indivisible with liberty and justice for all.

https://t.co/eqrs7KczJ7 At least now the truth has been made known publicly and clearly.  Praying for GOD’s Order to overtake and replace the garbage of the “Liberal World Order” - not only concerning higher gas prices, but what we’ve been dealing with over the past 2 1/2 years!
This is a huge win for the people, to move America toward energy independence again and to protect our energy grid. https://t.co/IZ6dyjNfRo

I’ve continually fought for more limited, accountable government - I am excited to see this SCOTUS ruling which limits the Federal EPA’s (Environmental Protection Agency) authority, they can no longer require changes in fuel sources related to energy generation.

It’s time to go back to the drawing board. This is good news for those who want to see a real I-5 solution to reduce traffic congestion - with NO tolls and NO light rail!

The entire validity of our election process is in question and at stake - not just for this election, but in the future as well. (3/3)

I believe there are enough valid questions about the integrity of the election process, how ballots were tallied and reported, that as a lawmaker you would have to question and reject the results and the electoral votes being counted today. (2/3)
As the Electoral College vote count process takes place in Wa.DC, I want to be very clear where I stand on the Nov. 3, 2020 elections and outcome. (1/3)
I look forward to serving the people of the 17th Legislative District as we move ahead. Thank you and may God bless you! (4/4)
My opponent had well over $300,000 spent on her behalf in the race vs. the $97,000 we had to work with. This is a testimony to the power of prayer and We The People! (3/4)

I also want to thank the LORD for His amazing faithfulness and for all the friends and volunteers who stood with me in prayer, sign waving, putting up signs, making calls, etc. I could not have won this race any other way! (2/4)
